JOHANNESBURG – Former Wits University student leader Mcebo Dlamini was been granted R2,000 bail by the Palm Ridge Magistrate Court on Wednesday morning. Dlamini was arrested last month in his room at the university residence on charges of public violence, theft, malicious damage to property and assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. However he was denied bail by the Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court, three days after his arrest. WATCH: Mcebo Dlamini granted bail The 30-year-old was appealing against a lower court’s decision. Judge Ratha Mokgoatlheng, of the Palm Ridge Magistrate Court said the lower court decision to deny Dlamini bail was wrong. One of Mokgoatlheng’s bail conditions for Dlamini, included that he should desist from disturbing academic activities at the university. #MceboDlamini tells me he is relieved with the court ruling eNCA